# Food App Backend

This is the backend API for a Food Ordering Application built using Node.js, Express.js, and MongoDB.

Features:
- User authentication
- Food item management
- API routes for users and food data
- MongoDB Atlas database integration
- RESTful API architecture

Tech Stack:
- Node.js
- Express.js
- MongoDB Atlas
- Mongoose
- REST API

How to Run:

1. Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/Rakshit4949/food-app.git

2. Install dependencies
npm install

3. Create a .env file and add MongoDB URI

4. Start the server
node server.js
